Description: Fragment of oval handle of Milesian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light purplish buff.
Curator's comments: Name Boton. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 206, 13, but chipped after he drew it. Not from the same die as the Miletus stamps, Archaeologische Anzeiger 2009 211, 10 and 11.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0070)
